text:
This stream was the final straw for me, I'm cancelling my memberships and dropping all Hololive streamers.  Its been coming for a long time, the way they dont moderate their chats, the way they HEAVILY restrict what the streamers can do on stream, the way they force JP into every aspect of their company and display obvious favoritism towards their JP streamers and audience, despite their biggest streamer being exclusively EN, truly makes for the single worst Vtuber company on the entire internet.

The way they restrict everything the streamers can do leads to vast swaths of their streamers playing one single game either exclusively or for huge amounts of time, which is no fun for anybody (anybody with a properly functioning brain, that is). It happens most with Apex, everybody is playing the damn plague of a 'game' and everytime a new botched Pokemon game drops, it is the only thing any of the 84 members play for months, again because they are so restricted in what they can do, they dont have a choice, they still HAVE to make content to drive the Holo-profit machine. 

Hololive is truly the worst entertainment corporation I can think of, sure there are movie companies that make garbage movies just for the payout, but even those movies are given attention. Hololive doesnt even hide the fact they only care about profits at the cost of their talents freedom and enjoyment

Gura alone has griped about the lack of things she can do on stream, up to being afraid to play Kookaburra sounds (wtf is Hololive afraid birds are going to sue them?!) and has admitted jealousy towards other Vtubers that can do whatever the hell they want because they arent chained to a Utilitarian corporation only concerned about how much money their streamers can rake in for them. The best thing Gura could do for her Vtuber career is leave Hololive, she would obviously take a vast portion of her fanbase with her, like she did when she went from being Senny to being Gura, everybody followed then, they will follow again. I know if she was allowed to be free and happy with her content, I would absolutely watch her and probably monetarily support her again.

The streamers are essentially the warehouse workers of Hololive, they do the most work, have to follow the most rules, and get into trouble the most easily. Not to mention I can only imagine how much income they funnel away from the girls into their own already stuffed pockets. They may very well just yoink every cent and then pay the streamers a portion of what they stole from the talent in the first place.

In short, screw you Hololive. You introduced me to Vtubers, and then swiftly displayed your incompetence as a streaming company. As quickly as I fell in love with Hololive, I fell straight back out of love, and directly into hate. Get it together.

text:
You have good aim for a new player. You just gotta learn how each weapon works and figure out what you like best. Play around in the firing range for a bit so you can play around with different stuff. Also, don't scoff at weapon attachments. They can make or break you in a fight. There are no attachments that will make a weapon worse, so just pick everything up. 

Basic looting tip: Take everything and swap things out as you get better stuff. There is no reason to be picky about your first weapon because you can change it later. A terrible weapon is still better than your fist.

I'll pass along a piece of advice that high tier battle royale players gave me: Set your mouse sensitivity as low as you can tolerate. Once you adapt you'll be surprised how precise your aim can get. ‚ñ°‚ñ°‚ñ°
